      description:
        "<p>Network Security is the protection of the underlying network infrastructure from unauthorized access, misuse, or theft. It involves creating a secure infrastructure for devices, applications, users, and applications to work securely.</p>\n\n<p><em>Key Competencies:</em></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Network and Routing Protocols / Services</strong> - Understanding of the OSI Model, the concepts of electronic data exchange, from signals in the wires, to modern data encryption techniques. Routing&nbsp; - Understanding of methodologies used to identify the optimal way of packet travel in the network.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Network Admin</strong> - Hands-on operation of a Computer Network and Equipment, Monitoring and Analyzing Network Traffic Flow, Patterns, and Performance. Hands-on Creation and Analysis of Critical Network Servers. VLANs and network troubleshooting best practices. Hands-on of Nmap.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Packet Tracer</strong> - Hands-on with Packet Tracer to design networks, configure switches, VLANs, Trunks, and Subnetting. Ability to configure LAN and WAN.&nbsp;</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Monitoring</strong> - Packet Level Traffic Analysis. Monitoring tools and introduction to SNMP.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Security Architecture</strong> - Good understanding of the Network security architecture. Can create/update/remove Firewalls, Antivirus, IDS/IPS, SIEM, DMZ and Honeypots. Hands-on with Snort IDS, Splunk. Hands-on of Windows Firewall and Linux iptables.</p>\n\t</li>\n</ol>\n",
